  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0ddd\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf \u0db8\u0ddc\u0d9c\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dc2\u0dd4 \u0dc4\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Somalia forces end Mogadishu hotel siege",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Somali forces have ended a deadly 30-hour siege of a hotel in the capital Mogadishu by al-Qaeda-linked militants, the security command has confirmed.",
        "\"The security forces have now completed the siege and the gunmen have been killed. We have not heard any firing from the building in the last hour,\" the commander said.",
        "He did not give further information on the total number of dead and said the government would hold a press conference this morning (21st). He added that the explosive devices still planted in the building need to be removed.",
        "Somali officials earlier said at least 13 civilians were killed and dozens wounded after militants launched a gun and bomb attack on the Hyatt Hotel on Friday evening.",
        "Meanwhile, the Wall Street Journal, citing two police officers, reported more than 20 deaths."
      ],
